snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard's Apology Video - Making Of
snippet.description:
Who says Australians make bad movies?
If you haven't seen the original: https://www.facebook.com/BarnabyJoyceMP/videos/524117514379871/
So this is the behind the scenes/making of. Or at least what it had to have been. Right?  Just to clarify:
Australia is a great country and I know the majority of us care about our biosecurity laws (as we should). This video is just to ask a few questions. Why was it made? What will it achieve? Are their performances quietly mocking Australian laws? Is it adequate punishment? Did I already own this hat? Did I try to write on both sides of the paper first?
